---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "chat-message"
description: "A single chat turn with role-based alignment, optional avatar support, sender metadata, and message state indicators."
elementName: chat-message
category: custom
currentPath: /docs/elements/custom-elements/chat-message/
permalink: /docs/elements/custom-elements/chat-message/
---

{% set userCode %}<chat-message data-role="user">
  <chat-bubble><p>Hello, I need help with my order.</p></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

{% set agentCode %}<chat-message data-role="agent" data-from-label="Sarah Chen">
  <user-avatar data-size="sm">
    <span data-fallback>SC</span>
  </user-avatar>
  <chat-bubble><p>Hi! I can look into that for you.</p></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

{% set systemCode %}<chat-message data-role="system">
  <chat-bubble>Sarah joined the conversation.</chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

{% set typingCode %}<chat-message data-role="agent" data-status="typing" data-from-label="Sarah Chen">
  <user-avatar data-size="sm">
    <span data-fallback>SC</span>
  </user-avatar>
  <chat-bubble></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

{% set modelCode %}<chat-message data-role="agent" data-from-label="Assistant" data-model="claude-sonnet-4-6">
  <chat-bubble><p>Here's what I found...</p></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

{% set errorCode %}<chat-message data-role="user" data-status="error">
  <chat-bubble><p>This message failed to send.</p></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

<browser-window
    src="/docs/examples/demos/chat-message-basic.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/chat-message"
    title="Chat Message Demo"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Represents a single conversation turn. Uses a grid layout to optionally accommodate a <code>&lt;user-avatar&gt;</code> alongside a <code>&lt;chat-bubble&gt;</code>. The <code>data-role</code> attribute controls alignment and bubble color.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-role</code></td>
          <td><code>user</code>, <code>agent</code>, <code>system</code></td>
          <td>Controls alignment and color</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-from</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Participant id (resolved by <code>chat-window</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-from-label</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Display name rendered via CSS <code>::before</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-status</code></td>
          <td><code>typing</code>, <code>sending</code>, <code>sent</code>, <code>error</code></td>
          <td>Message state</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-model</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>AI model identifier (informational)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-timestamp</code></td>
          <td>ISO 8601</td>
          <td>Message timestamp</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Layout Rules</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Role</th>
          <th>Alignment</th>
          <th>Bubble Style</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>user</code></td>
          <td>Right</td>
          <td>Primary color background</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>agent</code></td>
          <td>Left</td>
          <td>Sunken surface background</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>system</code></td>
          <td>Center</td>
          <td>Transparent, muted text</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>User Message</h2>
    <p>Right-aligned with primary color. No avatar needed.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="User message">{{ userCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Agent Message</h2>
    <p>Left-aligned with optional <code>&lt;user-avatar&gt;</code>. The <code>data-from-label</code> attribute renders a sender name above the bubble.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Agent message with avatar">{{ agentCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>System Message</h2>
    <p>Centered, full-width, with muted styling.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="System message">{{ systemCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Typing State</h2>
    <p>Set <code>data-status="typing"</code> and leave the <code>&lt;chat-bubble&gt;</code> empty. CSS renders animated dots. When content arrives, populate the bubble and remove the status attribute.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Typing indicator">{{ typingCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>The animation respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> and degrades to a static indicator.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Model Attribution</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-model</code> for AI contexts. This is informational metadata.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="AI model attribution">{{ modelCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Error State</h2>
    <p>Messages with <code>data-status="error"</code> receive an error border.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Error state">{{ errorCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Avatar Integration</h2>
    <p>Place a <code>&lt;user-avatar&gt;</code> as a direct child. The grid layout automatically creates a two-column arrangement. When no avatar is present, the layout collapses to a single column.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
